value.value: Any sensillum (UBERON:6007152) that is part of some larval head (UBERON:6001730).
Any sense organ (UBERON:6005155) that is part of some larval head (UBERON:6001730).

label.value: proximal-most point of head of femur

value.value: The proximal-most point of the head of a femur.

label.value: proximal-most point of head of humerus

value.value: The proximal-most point of the head of a humerus.

label.value: proximal-most point of ventral tubercle of humerus

value.value: The proximal-most point of the ventral tubercle of a humerus.

label.value: proximal-most point of greater trochanter of femur

value.value: The proximal-most point of the greater trochanter of a femur.
The tibial tuberosity is on the anterior side of a tibia and is where a patella ligament attaches.
An articular prominence of a talus that engages with the tibia.
Nasal bone on the left side of an organism when in anatomical position.
Nasal bone on the right side of an organism when in anatomical position.
Zygomatic arch on the left side of an organism when in anatomical position.
Zygomatic arch on the right side of an organism when in anatomical position.
A condyle on the distal end and lateral side of a radius.
A foramen of the skull found at either posterior angle of the hard palate, for the transmission of the descending palatine vessels and greater palatine nerve.

A foramen of the skull found at either posterior angle of the hard palate behind the greater palatine foramen. One or more lesser palatine foramina perforate the pyramidal process of the palatine bone and carry the lesser palatine nerve.
A raised projection on the calcaneus.
A suture joining a sphenoid bone with the alae of a vomer to form a schindylesis type of joint.
A suture joining the basisphenoid bone and the presphenoid bone of a sphenoid bone.

Region of retina around the fovea that extends approximately for 6 mm. Central retina is considerably thick due to increased density of photoreceptors, particularly cones and their associated bipolar and ganglion cells.
Left part of the organism dorsal to a horizontal plane and bounded on one side by the same transverse plane.
Right part of the organism dorsal to a horizontal plane and bounded on one side by the same transverse plane.

A collection of Purkinje fibers that receives signals from the right and left bundle branches and innervates the ventricular cardiac muscle. The Purkinje fiber network creates synchronized contractions of the heart ventricles.
A zone of skin that is part of a scalp.
A forelimb that is on the right side of a pectoral complex.
A forelimb that is on the left side of a pectoral complex.
A hindlimb that is on the right side of a pelvic complex.
A hindlimb that is on the left side of a pelvic complex.

Hepatic serous coat; peritoneal covering of the liver, enclosing almost all except for a triangular area on its posterior surface (the 'bare area of the liver') and a smaller area where the liver and gallbladder are in direct contact.
Subserosal tissue of liver. A zone of areolar connective tissue lying beneath the serous coat of the liver and distinguished with difficulty from the fibrous capsule of Glisson.
Region of liver parenchyma immediately below the capsule. This region is frequently specified in pathology diagnoses.
The anatomical junction between the duodenum and the jejunum.
Venule of villus of small intestine.
A lymphatic vessel that supplies the small intestine.

In human, ductal plate is a double-layered cylindrical structure of bile duct epithelium that surrounds the portal ramifications by the eighth gestational week. After approximately the 12th gestational week, remodelling of ductal plate begins, and maturity is attained by the end of gestation or early postnatal period.
Arteriole of villus of small intestine.
Submucous nerve plexus that is located in the anorectum.
Myenteric nerve plexus that is located in the anorectum.
A venule that is located in the anorectum.
An arteriole that is located in the anorectum.
A fringe of tissue around the ostium of the fallopian tube, in the direction of the ovary.
Myenteric nerve plexus that is located in the vermiform appendix.
Submucous nerve plexus that is located in the vermiform appendix.

A valve in an efferent lymphatic vessel. It manages the flow of lymphatic fluid out of the lymph node carrying immune cells and is essential for the correct flow of fluid through the lymphatic system.
An arteriole located in the colon.
The anatomical junction between the descending colon and the sigmoid colon.
A portal vein that drains the descending colon. It is a tributary of the inferior mesenteric vein, and follows the path of its corresponding artery, the left colic artery.
A portal vein that drains the ascending colon. It is a tributary of the superior mesenteric vein, and travels with its corresponding artery, the right colic artery.
The area where the jejunum ends and the ileum part of the intestine begins. Although there is no clear distinct section, the ileum is narrower and has smaller villi than the jejunum.
A venule located in the vermiform appendix.
The skin covering the inguinal region between the abdomen and the thigh on either side of the pubic bone.
